				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$B_{y}$\end{document} component) under general 3-D perturbations. This case can be reduced to analyzing stability with respect to ballooning modes alone. They found a general result that stability/instability was related to a general interchange criterion based on entropy: stability (instability) occurs for a tailward increase (decrease) of the entropy S=ln(pWγ)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
