The rationale for other plasma sheet transient definitions was largely dictated by the specific data analysis goals and data processing methods. One of the first terms emphasizing the transfer of flux, the Nightside Flux Transfer Events (NFTE) was introduced by Sergeev et al. (1992). Later definitions, emphasizing the rapid flux transport or RFT (Schödel et al. 2001), used the specific threshold value of the bursty convection electric field Ey>2mV/m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
