				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$V=400~\mbox{km}/\mbox{s}$\end{document}. The use of the electric field as a threshold marker helps trace the flux transport from the tail to the inner magnetosphere where the flow bursts are slowed down well below 400 km/s. A similar concept of Flux Pileup Regions (FPRs) was introduced by Zhang et al. (2007) and later used in a number of studies (e.g., Khotyaintsev et al. 2011) (see, also Sect. 4.4). Yet another definition emphasizes transient enhancements in Bz\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
