However, the plasmoid-chain instability and its predictions led to growth rates which, paradoxically, diverge with increasing Lundquist numbers. This was the basis for the studies carried out in Pucci and Velli (2014), where, via a linear analysis of the resistive tearing instability, it was shown that an aspect ratio scaling with a fractional power of S\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
